Indeed, about ⅔ of the world’s population speaks just 12 languages,

00:04:30.711 --> 00:04:35.951
out of the 7,000 or so different languages that exist in the world.

00:04:37.051 --> 00:04:47.231
So almost 70% of the population speaks a total of less than 0.2% of the languages in the world.

00:04:48.281 --> 00:04:54.451
You can probably guess the most dominant languages - there's Mandarin, Spanish, English,

00:04:54.701 --> 00:05:01.981
Hindi, Bengali, Portuguse, Russian, Japanese, Western Punjabi, Marathi, Telugu, and Wu Chinese.

00:05:02.541 --> 00:05:09.701
These languages have come to dominate, and endanger the other almost 7,000 languages.

00:05:10.441 --> 00:05:13.361
You might say, well, it’s only natural.

00:05:13.961 --> 00:05:20.371
As more people speak a certain language, it’s understandable that people want their

00:05:20.381 --> 00:05:25.311
children to speak that language, so they stop speaking their own language at home,

00:05:25.611 --> 00:05:32.121
and thus these other languages eventually die out as people choose not to use them.

